  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have legal frameworks to combat money laundering. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. International frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Typical legal requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n3. Enforcement mechanisms\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Licensing restrictions for financial institutions\n\n4. Common legal provisions\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Counter-terrorism financing regulations\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors\n\n5. Key regulatory bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income through complex financial transactions.",
